file;unicode	channel;int	start;float	end;float	speaker;unicode	speakerType;unicode	speakerDialect;unicode	transcript;unicode	section;int	turn;int	segment;int	sectionType;unicode	suType;unicodeXIN_CMN_20080726.0015	0	300.0	400.0	speaker	unknown	unknown	A circle of bristle was pasted on the bottom of the feet of the five Olympic mascots, "Fu Wa" and they were put in the center of a copper plate. The old artist, Bai Dacheng, was from the "Museum Home" of No. 1 Dongguanfang Hutong, Shichahai, Beijing. With his rhythmic beating around the copper plate, "bristled" Fu Wa of various shapes started to dance with joy...	0	0	0		XIN_CMN_20080726.0015	0	500.0	600.0	speaker	unknown	unknown	The "Bristled man" performance is an intangible cultural heritage in Beijing, a unique skill among old Beijing performances of folk arts. It appeared in the late Qing dynasty, and has been around for more than a hundred years. It was born with the influence of Peking operas and shadow plays.	0	0	0		XIN_CMN_20080726.0015	0	600.0	700.0	speaker	unknown	unknown	To make a "bristled man," its head and base are made of plaster, the body frame is made of sorghum stalks, wrapped with colored paper (or colored silk) cloak and some added cotton. Then the face and clothes are painted based on the characters in the stories, a circle of pork bristles of two to three centimeters is pasted around the base, that's why they are called "bristled man."	0	0	0		XIN_CMN_20080726.0015	0	1000.0	1100.0	speaker	unknown	unknown	In 1915, Beijing "bristled man" took part in the "Panama International Exposition," it received a silver award and has become famous since then.	0	0	0		XIN_CMN_20080726.0015	0	1500.0	1600.0	speaker	unknown	unknown	Bai Dacheng told reporters that, under the theme "Everybody protects cultural heritage, and everybody enjoys the fruit of protection" today, apart from "elegant" culture and elite culture, more and more people are paying attention to folk cultural heritage that has distinct national and regional characters.	0	0	0		XIN_CMN_20080726.0015	0	1600.0	1700.0	speaker	unknown	unknown	Nowadays, people keep knocking on the door of the "Museum Home" of No. 1 Dongguanfang Hutong, Shichahai and as the master of this place, I see more and more "bristled man" performances moving from folk arts to outside the country. Chinese cultural heritage protection is constantly moving toward people, toward the public.	0	0	0		